# LxveAce Tag Studio
## End-User License Agreement (EULA)

**IMPORTANT: PLEASE READ THIS AGREEMENT CAREFULLY BEFORE DOWNLOADING, INSTALLING, OR USING LXVEACE TAG STUDIO.**

### 1. GRANT OF LICENSE

LxveAce ("Licensor") grants you a non-exclusive, non-transferable, limited license to use LxveAce Tag Studio ("Software") on a single designated computer, subject to the terms of this Agreement. This is a license to use the Software, not a sale. Licensor retains all ownership, copyright, and intellectual property rights.

### 2. EVALUATION LICENSE

#### 2.1 Trial Period
Upon installation, you receive a thirty (30) day evaluation license at no cost. During this period, you may use the Software for evaluation and testing purposes only.

#### 2.2 Expiration
After the thirty (30) day evaluation period, the Software will enter a limited mode:
- Canvas editing remains available
- Export is disabled
- Machine connectivity is disabled
- A license key prompt will appear on startup

#### 2.3 License Key Activation
To restore full functionality, you must obtain a valid Commercial License (Section 3) and activate it with a license key provided by Licensor.

### 3. COMMERCIAL LICENSE

#### 3.1 Purchase & Activation
To continue using the Software after the evaluation period, you must purchase a Commercial License. Commercial licenses are sold on a per-seat, per-year basis at Licensor's standard rates. Upon purchase, you will receive a license key. Activation is automatic upon entry of a valid key in the Software settings.

#### 3.2 License Tiers
Licensor offers the following license tiers (subject to change):
- **Solo**: Single user, single machine
- **Team**: 2–5 users, unlimited machines
- **Enterprise**: 6+ users, unlimited machines, priority support

See [lxveace.com/pricing](https://lxveace.com/pricing) for current terms and pricing.

#### 3.3 Renewal
Commercial Licenses must be renewed annually. Licensor will provide renewal notices at least thirty (30) days before expiration. Failure to renew will cause the Software to revert to limited mode.

### 4. RESTRICTIONS

You may **NOT**:
- Reverse-engineer, decompile, disassemble, or attempt to derive the source code of the Software
- Modify, adapt, translate, or create derivative works based on the Software
- Sublicense, sell, rent, lease, transfer, assign, or lend the Software
- Remove or alter any copyright, trademark, or proprietary notices
- Use the Software for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any applicable law
- Use the Software on more than one computer simultaneously (except as expressly permitted in a Team/Enterprise license)
- Share your license key with other users
- Use the Software to provide labeling services to third parties without a separate licensing agreement

### 5. DATA & PRIVACY

#### 5.1 Local Storage
The Software processes and stores label designs, templates, and data files locally on your computer. Licensor does not access, collect, or transmit this data unless you explicitly authorize export to a machine or cloud service.

#### 5.2 No Telemetry
The Software contains no telemetry, analytics, or usage tracking features. You have full control over your data.

#### 5.3 Credentials
Machine credentials (API keys, auth tokens) are stored in your operating system's credential store (Windows DPAPI, macOS Keychain, Linux Secret Service) and are never transmitted to Licensor without your explicit request for support.

### 6. MACHINE ADAPTERS

The Software includes adapters for third-party machines (Trotec, Panduit, Roland, etc.). Use of these adapters is subject to the terms of service and licensing agreements of those vendors. Licensor is not responsible for third-party hardware failures, data loss, or licensing disputes with vendors.

